External knowledge:
- "Performance in various financial and demographic metrics" refers to the institution's ranking based on graduate debt, mean earnings, median earnings, debt-to-income ratio, tuition fees, total cost, total enrollment, graduation rate, student-to-faculty ratio, and underrepresented minority percentages;
- "Better performance" for some metrics (e.g., graduate debt, debt-to-income ratio, tuition fees) means lower values, while for others (e.g., mean earnings, median earnings, total enrollment, graduation rate), it means higher values;
- Institutions with lower rankings in certain metrics and higher rankings in others are considered to have better overall performance.
